h3. Issue Summary

Applying a code suggestion made in the [pull request comment|https://confluence.atlassian.com/bitbucketserver/commenting-on-a-pull-request-1027119882.html] makes CRLF to LF.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Commit a test.txt file with content {{a\rb\r\nc}}
It should look like
{code:java}
$ hexdump test.txt
0000000 61 0d 62 0d 0a 63
{code}
 # Create a pull request for the file above
 # Apply suggestion on the second line to be {{bbb}}
!Screen Shot 2022-01-05 at 11.35.27.png|width=553,height=284!

h3. Expected Results

The file should be {{a\rbbb\r\nc}}
i.e.
{code:java}
$ hexdump test.txt
0000000 61 0d 62 62 62 0d 0a 63
{code}
h3. Actual Results

The carriage returns {{0d}} are removed and line feed was converted as LF {{0a}} instead of the original CRLF {{0d 0a}}
{code:java}
$ hexdump test.txt
0000000 61 0a 62 62 62 0a 63
{code}
h3. Workaround

{{LineReplacingOutputStream.class}} need to be patched.

{panel:title=Questions about Apache Log4j 2 CVE-2021-44228|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3c78b5|titleBGColor=#3c78b5|bgColor=#e7f4fa}
If you have questions about Apache Log4j 2 CVE-2021-44228 or CVE-2021-45105 please raise a support case via [https://getsupport.atlassian.com|https://getsupport.atlassian.com/]
{panel}
Bitbucket Server currently bundles Elasticsearch 6.8.6 in 6.10 LTS. On account of CVE-2021-44228 and CVE-2021-45105 Elasticsearch should be updated to 6.8.22.

Note that Bitbucket Server 6.10.16 already contains mitigations (see [BSERV-13088|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/BSERV-13088]), but now Elasticsearch 6.8.22 is available with patched log4j the bundled version should be updated.

{panel:title=Important: Elasticsearch license change|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3c78b5|titleBGColor=#3c78b5|bgColor=#e7f4fa}
Note that Elasticsearch versions from 7.11 onwards are no longer available licensed under the Apache 2.0 open source license. See [here|https://www.elastic.co/pricing/faq/licensing] and  [here|https://www.elastic.co/blog/elastic-license-v2] for details of the new licensing.
{panel}

Support for using Elasticsearch 7.16.2 with Bitbucket Server & Data Center should be added on account of CVE-2021-44228 and CVE-2021-45105.

Note: The scope of this issue does not include bundling Elasticsearch 7.16.2 with Bitbucket, rather just just usage as an external/self-managed service, as is required when running Bitbucket in a cluster. Due to the licensing change Atlassian is not able to bundle Elasticsearch 7.16.

h3. Issue Summary

TypeScript syntax coloring error with Literal and parentheses. After `) errors continue to end of file.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a file with the extension .ts on a new branch.
 # Add `) to the file. Examples:
 ** 
{noformat}
a(m) {
	t(${t()}`);
}

a(m) {
	t(${t()});
}
{noformat}

 ** 
{noformat}
a(m) {
	t(`${t()}` );
}

a(m) {
	t(${t()});
}
{noformat}

 # Create a pull request.
 # View the file in the pull request.
 # View entire source of file.

h3. Expected Results

The color coding will work for the whole file.
h3. Actual Results

Color coding from the Literal close parentheses makes the rest of the file coded incorrectly.
h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

{panel:title=Questions about Apache Log4j 2 CVE-2021-44228|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#3c78b5|titleBGColor=#3c78b5|bgColor=#e7f4fa}
If you have questions about Apache Log4j 2 CVE-2021-44228 please raise a support case via [https://getsupport.atlassian.com|https://getsupport.atlassian.com/]
For more information about CVE-2021-44228 see the security advisory [Multiple Products Security Advisory - Log4j Vulnerable To Remote Code Execution - CVE-2021-44228|https://confluence.atlassian.com/security/multiple-products-security-advisory-log4j-vulnerable-to-remote-code-execution-cve-2021-44228-1103069934.html]
{panel}
{panel:title=IMPORTANT NOTES|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#b53c3c|titleBGColor=#b53c3c|bgColor=#f2bbbb}
 * This patch is only effective for the Linux and MacOS operating system. If you are hosting Bitbucket on Windows the below described mitigation (i.e. jvm.options updates) should be applied manually and the Elasticsearch service should be restarted.
 * This patch only effects the bundled Elasticsearch. If you are running a separate Elasticsearch instance (for example because Bitbucket is running in a multi-node cluster), you should consult [Elastic security advisory ESA-2021-31|https://discuss.elastic.co/t/apache-log4j2-remote-code-execution-rce-vulnerability-cve-2021-44228-esa-2021-31/291476] to determine if any action is required to mitigate CVE-2021-44228{panel}
Bitbucket Server and Data Center include a bundled Elasticsearch, this may or not be used depending on how Bitbucket is configured. Specifically:
 * By default Bitbucket will start the bundled Elasticsearch
 * If Bitbucket is started with the {{--no-search}} parameter then the bundled Elasticsearch is not started. This is common for Bitbucket clusters, where an external Elasticsearch must be used, one that is used by all nodes of the cluster.

The vendor has made the following announcement regarding CVE-2021-44228: [https://discuss.elastic.co/t/apache-log4j2-remote-code-execution-rce-vulnerability-cve-2021-44228-esa-2021-31/291476]
{quote}Elasticsearch 6 and 7 are not susceptible to remote code execution with this vulnerability due to our use of the Java Security Manager. Elasticsearch running on JDK8 or below is susceptible to an information leak via DNS which is fixable by the JVM option identified below.
{quote}
More details are supplied in that document in the section "Details on Elasticsearch information leakage".

The mitigation for the above mentioned information leak involves passing {{-Dlog4j2.formatMsgNoLookups=true}} to the JVM that runs Elasticsearch. This should be applied to the startup scripts Bitbucket ships.

If you are unable to install an updated version of Bitbucket Server, make the following change to the Elasticsearch JVM options file then restart Bitbucket Server:

Add the following line to the bottom of the file {{$BITBUCKET_HOME/shared/search/jvm.options}}
{code:java}
-Dlog4j2.formatMsgNoLookups=true
{code}

h4. New feature request

Add support for connecting to a PostgreSQL database with SSL

e.g. adding the {{?ssl=true}} parameter to the JDBC URL for connecting to the DB:
{code:java}
jdbc.url=jdbc:postgresql://dbhost:5432/bitbucket?ssl=true
{code}
